headline: Airlines set for a smoother 2026, BMO says
summary: Investing.com -- BMO Capital Markets has initiated coverage on the U.S. airline sector with a constructive outlook for 2026, arguing that the industry is finally emerging from “a challenging 2024–2025” marked by excess domestic capacity and weak corporate travel.
